---
description: CourseHub Go architecture & style rules
globs: ["**/*.go"]
alwaysApply: true
---

- Layered architecture: dependencies point inward to `internal/domain`.
- `service` depends only on interfaces it declares in `internal/service/ports.go`;
  inject concrete `storage` implementations in `cmd/server`.
- Define small (1–3 method) interfaces where they are consumed.
- Grading schemes: add a `grading.Strategy` type and register it — no switches elsewhere.
- Grading reactions: add a `progress.Observer` and subscribe it in `cmd/server`.
- Build courses via `course.Factory`, never construct `base` directly.
- gofmt/goimports; wrap errors with `%w`; compare via `errors.Is/As`; use
  sentinel errors from `internal/domain`.
- `ctx context.Context` first parameter; never stored in structs.
- Table-driven tests with `t.Run` subtests, stdlib `testing` only, ≥ 70% coverage.
